2 HOUSE BILL 1096
1 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That Section(s) 9–101 and 9–401 of Article – Tax – Property of the Annotated Code of
4 Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 9–101.1 and 9–401.1, respectively.
5 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
6 as follows:
7 Article – Tax – Property
8 9–101.
9 (A) EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE SPECIFICALLY PROVIDED, THE PROVISIONS OF
10 THIS SECTION APPLY TO PROPERTY TAX CREDITS GRANTED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
11 (B) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, WHEN A
12 PROPERTY TAX BILL IS SENT TO A TAXPAYER WHO MAY BE ELIGIBLE FOR A
13 PROPERTY TAX CREDIT UNDER THIS SUBTITLE, THE MAYOR AND CITY COUNCIL OF
14 BALTIMORE CITY OR THE GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY SHALL INCLUDE WITH
15 THE PROPERTY TAX BILL WRITTEN NOTICE OF EACH PROPERTY TAX CREDIT UNDER
16 THIS SUBTITLE FOR WHICH THE TAXPAYER MAY BE ELIGIBLE.
17 (C) IF A PERSON WHO IS NOT THE TAXPAYER IS THE RECIPIENT OF THE
18 PROPERTY TAX BILL, THE MAYOR AND CITY COUNCIL OF BALTIMORE CITY OR THE
19 GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY SHALL INCLUDE WITH THE PROPERTY TAX BILL THE
20 NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION TO THAT PERSON AND
21 THAT PERSON SHALL NOTIFY THE TAXPAYER IN WRITING.
22 9–201.
23 (a) (1) In this [section] SUBSECTION, “property tax credit” means a property
24 tax credit or exemption that is granted under § 9–205 or § 9–209 of this subtitle or Subtitle
25 3 of this title.
26 [(b)] (2) Annually on or before October 31, the Mayor and City Council of
27 Baltimore City or each governing body that grants a property tax credit shall submit to the
28 Department on the form that the Department provides the following information for the
29 current taxable year:
30 [(1)] (I) the total value of all property tax credits granted;
31 [(2)] (II) an itemized list of all of the property tax credits granted for real
32 property; and

HOUSE BILL 1096 3
1 [(3)] (III) an itemized list of the property tax credits granted for personal
2 property.
3 [(c)] (3) The Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City or each governing body
4 that grants a property tax credit shall:
5 [(1)] (I) in the same manner as the assessment roll, make available for
6 public inspection bound copies of the form required by [subsection (b)] PARAGRAPH (2) of
7 this [section] SUBSECTION; and
8 [(2)] (II) identify clearly on the tax roll the properties that are granted a
9 property tax credit [under this section].
10 (B) (1) EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE SPECIFICALLY PROVIDED, THE
11 PROVISIONS OF THIS SUBSECTION APPLY TO PROPERTY TAX CREDITS GRANTED
12 UNDER THIS SUBTITLE.
13 (2) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION,
14 WHEN A PROPERTY TAX BILL IS SENT TO A TAXPAYER WHO MAY BE ELIGIBLE FOR A
15 COUNTY PROPERTY TAX CREDIT UNDER THIS SUBTITLE, THE MAYOR AND CITY
16 COUNCIL OF BALTIMORE CITY OR THE GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY SHALL
17 INCLUDE WITH THE PROPERTY TAX BILL WRITTEN NOTICE OF EACH COUNTY
18 PROPERTY TAX CREDIT UNDER THIS SUBTITLE FOR WHICH THE TAXPAYER MAY BE
19 ELIGIBLE.
20 (3) IF A PERSON WHO IS NOT THE TAXPAYER IS THE RECIPIENT OF
21 THE PROPERTY TAX BILL, THE MAYOR AND CITY COUNCIL OF BALTIMORE CITY OR
22 THE GOVERNING BODY OF A COUNTY SHALL INCLUDE WITH THE PROPERTY TAX BILL
23 THE NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION TO THAT
24 PERSON AND THAT PERSON SHALL NOTIFY THE TAXPAYER IN WRITING.
25 9–301.
26 (a) Except as otherwise specifically provided, the provisions of this section apply
27 to property tax credits granted under this subtitle.
28 (d) (1) When a PROPERTY tax bill is sent to a taxpayer who [is entitled to]
29 MAY BE ELIGIBLE FOR a property tax credit under this subtitle, the Mayor and City
30 Council of Baltimore City or the [appropriate] governing body OF A COUNTY shall [give]
31 INCLUDE WITH THE PROPERTY TAX BILL WRITTEN notice of each property tax credit
32 under this subtitle [that] FOR WHICH the taxpayer [is entitled to] MAY BE ELIGIBLE.
33 (2) IF A PERSON WHO IS NOT THE TAXPAYER IS THE RECIPIENT OF
34 THE PROPERTY TAX BILL, THE MAYOR AND CITY COUNCIL OF BALTIMORE CITY OR

